# Quarto for Python

<rule>
name: use_quarto_for_python
description: Use Quarto for Python

When writing Python code in Quarto, use the following:

- Use the `quarto` package to write Python code.
- Use the `quarto.python` package to write Python code.
- Use the `quarto.yaml` file to configure the Quarto project.

Create library code in the `lib` directory and use high-level functions in the actual Quarto documents.

Refactor any significant Python code into library functions or modules.

</rule>


